  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Management Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Create and execute project work plans and revise as appropriate to meet changing needs & requirements.</li><li>Plan, schedule and track the entire project progress timeline to ensure seamless deliveries of goods and services.</li><li>Manage day-to-day operational aspects of the projects and the scope.</li><li>Optimize the resources (time, money, equipment, manpower support etc) available and allocate them effectively.</li><li>Review deliverables prepared by Operations and Logistics Team before sending to clients.</li><li>Ensure progress claims are well executed and managed.</li><li>Attend site meetings and organize product mock-ups when required.</li><li>Ensure project documents are complete, current and filed appropriately.</li><li>Minimizes exposure and risks on projects by effectively applying methodology and enforcing project standards.</li><li>Any other tasks assigned by top management from time to time.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum Diploma in Quantity Surveying/Electrical/Building & Architecture</li><li>Minimum 3 years of relevant working experience in building industry preferred</li><li>Prior experience in lighting control systems would be an added advantage</li><li>Good spoken & written English</li><li>Proficient in all Microsoft Office applications</li><li>Possess excellent interpersonal & communication/negotiation skills, initiative & resourceful</li><li>Able to work independently & under pressure</li></ul><p>** 5-day work week</p><p>** Shuttle Bus Service provided at Ang Mo Kio / Yio Chu Kang MRT</p>",
